  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1978-02-27", 
    "text": "Journalists' Freedom of Choice Act - Amends the National Labor Relations Act to state that, notwithstanding provisions which declare bargaining representatives chosen by a majority of employees in a bargaining unit to be exclusive representatives, any individual who is employed as a columnist, broadcast journalist, commentator, or critic on public issues shall have the right to bargain, present grievances, and contract without the participation of or intervention of bargaining representatives."
